  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your oven-proof dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-creamy-cauliflower-cheese-with-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Wash, then remove the <strong>leaves</strong> from your <strong>cauliflower[s]</strong> and reserve them for later</p><p>Slice the <strong>cauliflower[s]</strong> into 1<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>steak per person, approx. 3cm thick (use the middle part as it's larger)</p><p>Tip: Save any leftover florets for another recipe!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-creamy-cauliflower-cheese-with-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cauliflower steak[s]</strong> to<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>a large <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>(or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into wedges and add them to the dish[es]</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry</strong> <strong>tomatoes</strong> roughly</p><p>Put the dish[es] in the oven for an initial 30 min or until golden</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-creamy-cauliflower-cheese-with-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Mix the<strong> grated cheese</strong> with your<strong> cornflour </strong>in a jug</p><p>Add your<strong> creamy single soy</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(not a mustard fan? Go easy!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up until well combined – this is your <strong>cheese sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-creamy-cauliflower-cheese-with-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-creamy-cauliflower-cheese-with-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the cauliflower is golden, remove the dish[es] from the oven, flip the steak[s] over and give the potatoes a good mix up</p><p>Pour the <strong>cheese sauce </strong>all over</p><p>Return the dish[es] to the oven for a further 12-15 min or until bubbling and thickened – this is your <strong>all-in-one creamy cauliflower cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-creamy-cauliflower-cheese-with-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>cauliflower leaves</strong> to a separate baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and put the tray[s] in the oven for 5-8 min or until crispy</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes</strong> to the<strong> salad </strong>and drizzle<strong> </strong>over your<strong> red wine vinegar </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> – this is your<strong> dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/all-in-one-creamy-cauliflower-cheese-with-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve<strong> </strong>the <strong>creamy cauliflower cheese </strong>with the<strong> dressed salad</strong> and <strong>crispy cauliflower leaves </strong>to the side</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
